---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Jeff Conners" description="About the artist and process behind the collection.">
  <section class="hero" style="min-height: 34vh;">
    <p class="section-label">About</p>
    <h1>
      Painting from perspective,
      <span class="accent">not convention.</span>
    </h1>
    <p>
      Jeff Conners approaches composition through contrast, line tension, and layered value. Color choices
      are intentional, often driven by perception differences that lead to surprising combinations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="two-col">
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="section-label">Process</p>
      <p>
        Work starts with shape studies and tonal sketches, then moves into acrylic and mixed-media sessions.
        The final pieces balance strong geometry with organic texture.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="section-label">Vision</p>
      <p>
        The goal is simple: build room for the art itself. Minimal interface, large format imagery, and
        clear metadata keep focus where it belongs.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

